# This demo reads NO credentials from the environment.
#
# It's a testing harness for inTrack dashboards, so panel type (VAPID or Firebase)
# and all inTrack SDK keys are entered at runtime on the in-app Setup page
# (/setup) and stored in the browser's localStorage:
#
#   - VAPID panels:    App Key, Auth Key, Public Key, environment, debug
#   - Firebase panels: App Key, Auth Key, environment, debug
#                      (+ Firebase project config on the Push: Firebase page)
#
# Use "Reset demo" on the Setup page to wipe the stored values. No .env.local needed.
